SIMPLE: strive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strive
<hw>Strive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos>
<conjf>Strove</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Striven</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> (<mark>Rarely</mark>,
<conjf>Strove</conjf>); <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Striving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>estriver</ets>; of
Teutonic origin, and akin to G. <ets>streben</ets>, D.
<ets>streven</ets>, Dan. <ets>straebe</ets>, Sw. <ets>str⟦aum⟧fva</ets>.
Cf. <er>Strife</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make efforts; to use
exertions; to endeavor with earnestness; to labor hard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Was for this his ambition <qex>strove</qex>⟦br⟧
To equal Caesar first, and after, Jove?</q>
<rj><qau>Cowley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To struggle in opposition; to be in contention or
dispute; to contend; to contest; -- followed by <xex>against</xex> or
<xex>with</xex> before the person or thing opposed; <as>as,
<ex>strive</ex> against temptation; <ex>strive</ex> for the
truth</as>.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My Spirit shall not always <qex>strive</qex> with man.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. vi. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why dost thou <qex>strive</qex> against him?</q> <rj><qau>Job
xxxiii. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now private pity <qex>strove</qex> with public hate,⟦br⟧
Reason with rage, and eloquence with fate.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To vie; to compete; to be a rival.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Not] that sweet grove⟦br⟧
Of Daphne, by Orontes and the inspired⟦br⟧
Castalian spring, might with this paradise⟦br⟧
Of Eden <qex>strive</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To contend; vie; struggle; endeavor;
aim.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Strive
<hw>Strive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An effort; a
striving.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Strife; contention.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Wyclif (luke xxi. 9).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strived</ent>⟦br⟧
